## Overview
Scenario analysis is a strategic planning method used to explore and evaluate possible future events by considering alternative potential outcomes.

## Purpose
The purpose of scenario analysis is to enhance adaptability, resilience, and foresight in decision-making by identifying opportunities and mitigating risks. It helps organizations navigate complex futures and make informed decisions about their long-term strategic direction.

## How it works
To use scenario analysis, define the scope and purpose of your analysis, identify key drivers and uncertainties that could impact your subject of concern. Develop a range of plausible scenarios, each representing a different future state based on varying combinations of drivers and uncertainties. Analyze the potential impacts of each scenario on your subject in question/objectives, identifying opportunities, risks, and strategic implications.

## Requirements
Scenario analysis requires participants to be fairly open-minded and imaginative. It should ideally be carried out over an extended time period to unpack all aspects of the scenario. The process involves research, surveys, workshops, analysis, reports, and review, which can take several weeks or even months.

## Reflections
When using scenario analysis for R&D purposes, keep in mind that it is a dynamic and critical component of strategic foresight. It helps organizations challenge their assumptions and explore the implications of different strategic choices.

## Related methods (if any)
Scenario analysis is related to Collective Intelligence, Foresight, and Future Analysis.
